Here is a general example of a worldtoscreen function implementation in C++. It assumes that you are working with a 2D coordinate system and that there is a known screen size and viewport.

```cpp
// Function to convert world coordinates to screen coordinates
void worldToScreen(float worldX, float worldY, float& screenX, float& screenY) {
    // Calculate the scaling factors for converting world coordinates to screen coordinates
    float scaleWidth = screen_width / (view_right - view_left);
    float scaleHeight = screen_height / (view_bottom - view_top);

    // Convert world coordinates to screen coordinates
    screenX = (worldX - view_left) * scaleWidth;
    screenY = (worldY - view_top) * scaleHeight;
}
```

